    streamFind for mass spectrometry with R

msData R6 class and methods

Source: R/class_R6_msData.R
msData.Rd

The msData R6 class is a framework with methods for parsing, processing, visualizing and storing MS data.

Method new()

Checks the analyses argument as a character/integer vector to match analyses names or indices from the msData object. Returns a valid character vector with analysis names or NULL for non-matching.

Creates an msData class object. When headers are not given (i.e., NULL), a default headers S3 class object is generated with name as NA_character, path as get_wd() and date as Sys.time(). See ?headers for more information.

Usage

msData$new(
  files = NULL,
  runParallel = FALSE,
  headers = NULL,
  settings = NULL,
  analyses = NULL,
  groups = NULL,
  alignment = NULL
)

Arguments

files

A character vector with full file path/s of mzML or mzXML file/s or a data.frame with the columns file, replicate and blank with the full file path of mzML or mzXML file/s (character), the replicate group name (character) and the associated blank replicate group name (character). Note the file paths must have the extension .mzML or .mzXML.

runParallel

Logical length one. Set to TRUE for parallel processing. Note that parallel processing is not always faster due to overhead.

headers

A named list with headers or a headers S3 class object. Each list element must have length one. There is not type restrictions except for name (must be type character), path (must be type character) and date (must be class POSIXct or class POSIXt). See more information in ?headers.

settings

A settings S3 class object or a list with settings S3 class objects as elements (see ?settings for more information).

settings

A settings S3 class object or a list with settings S3 class objects as elements (see ?settings for more information).

analyses

X.

groups

data.table with feature groups from correspondence across MS analyses as obtained by the msData method get_groups(). Note that correspondence of features across MS analyses is performed with the method group_features() from the msData class.

groups

data.table with feature groups from correspondence across MS analyses as obtained by the msData method get_groups(). Note that correspondence of features across MS analyses is performed with the method group_features() from the msData class.

alignment

X.

Returns

A new msData class object.

Method get_spectra()

Method to get spectra from the MS analyses.

Usage

msData$get_spectra(
  analyses = NULL,
  levels = NULL,
  mz = NULL,
  rt = NULL,
  ppm = 20,
  sec = 60,
  id = NULL,
  allTraces = TRUE,
  isolationWindow = 1.3,
  minIntensityMS1 = 0,
  minIntensityMS2 = 0,
  runParallel = FALSE
)

Arguments

analyses

X.

levels

Name.

mz

X.

rt

X.

ppm

X.

sec

X.

id

X.

allTraces

Logical, when TRUE all level 2 data is returned. When FALSE and level has 2, only the MS2 traces of MS1 targets are returned, using the isolationWindow to calculate the mass window.

isolationWindow

X.

minIntensityMS1

X.

minIntensityMS2

X.

runParallel

X.

Returns

A data.frame with spectra for each analyses and targets when defined.

Method add_headers()

Method to add headers information to the msData object. If an argument or element name is given, it must be type character. If an argument or element path is given, it must be type character and exist. If an argument or element date is given, it must be class POSIXct or POSIXt. If given date is character, conversion to class POSIXct or POSIXt is attempted. See ?headers for more information.

Usage

msData$add_headers(...)

Arguments

...

Arguments to be added as headers. Note that all given arguments must be of length one. There is not type limitation. The name of the argument becomes the name of the header entry. Alternatively, a single list argument with the headers (all length one) can be given.

Returns

Invisible.

Method find_features()

Finds features (i.e., chromatographic peaks) from MS data in an msData class object. The function uses the patRoon package for peak finding, enabling the use of several algorithms (see details). Note that the settings call name must be "find_features".

Usage

msData$find_features(settings = NULL)

Arguments

settings

A list object with call name, algorithm and parameters. When not given, settings will be searched within the msData object.

Details

See the findFeatures function from the patRoon package or the reference guide for more information. The following algorithms are available via patRoon: "xcms3", "xcms", "openms", "envipick", "sirius", "kpic2", "safd". The algorithm in the settings should be one of the described. The parameters are given as a list and should match with algorithm requirements. Certain algorithms also require defined MS file formats and data in profile mode.

Returns

Invisible.

Method group_features()

Groups and aligns features across analyses in the msData object. The function uses the patRoon package for grouping features, enabling the use of several algorithms (see details). Note that the settings call name must be "group_features".

Usage

msData$group_features(settings = NULL)

Arguments

settings

A list object with call name, algorithm and parameters. When not given, settings will be searched within the msData object.

Details

See the groupFeatures function from the patRoon package or the reference guide for more information. The following algorithms are possible: "xcms3", "xcms", "openms" or "kpic2". The algorithm slot in the settings should be one of the described. The parameters are given as a list and should match with algorithm requirements.

Returns

Invisible.
